Create the HTML structure with a main container for the slider.

Add three hidden radio buttons that keep track of which slide is active.

Create a slides container that holds three slides side-by-side.

Use CSS flexbox to arrange slides horizontally.

Move the slides container left or right using CSS transform based on which radio button is checked.

Add labels as buttons for previous and next controls, linked to the radio buttons to change slides when clicked.

Add navigation dots as labels linked to each radio button for direct slide selection.

Style each slide with different background colors and text.

Make the layout responsive to fit mobile screens nicely.

Add accessibility attributes so keyboard and screen readers can navigate the slider.
